1 The allusion is to the disastrous defeat of Pompey by Julius Caesar at the battle of Pharsalia in Thessaly, 48 B.c.

² Dante reproaches the Lombards with their barbarian origin, in allusion to their supposed descent through the Longobards from a Scandinavian tribe (see below).

³ Cf. I'nf. xv. 75-83 xxvi. 60 (where the Trojans are referred to as ‘il gentil seme de’ Romani ³) ; Com. iv. 4, ll. 103-53 Mon. ii. 11, ll. 22-4.
